This pull request just made my day
. This could go with the pull, or it could go with the actual script but I thought I should mention it.
We need a way to detect clipping and automatically shift to left/right alignment. Here is the problem image:

So when it clips, it should be auto-detected. Personally, I'm running a debounce script from http://unscriptable.com/index.php/2009/03/20/debouncing-javascript-methods/ and tying screen measurements into it but that's just one solution. I have the luxury of knowing the exact pixel range where my project clips, for this you'll need something a bit more universal.
The obvious resolution though, is to flip to top left in this example, when the issue occurs:

Then in mobile views, I do something else entirely:

So again, this should probably be its own issue but since it's magnified by adding the additional two items, it also fits here.
Food for thought.
. Good to know. In the meantime I just put a document width check on the body and did
function setSocial() {
        var social = $('.social');
        if(screenwidth >= 769 && screenwidth <= 1181 ) {
            if(social.hasClass('center')) {
                social.removeClass('center').addClass('left');
            }
        } else {
            if(social.hasClass('left')) {
                social.removeClass('left').addClass('center');
            }
        }
    }
But for a wider implementation, I think the linked project would match well with this script.
